The South African Communist Party in the Western Cape staged an illegal protest at the Cape Town Convention Centre (CTICC). The party was calling for the resignation of the entire Eskom board. Eskom CEO Brian Molefe was expected to address the African Utility Week at the CTICC this morning but unexpectedly cancelled his appearance. Provincial South African Communist Party secretary Benson Ngqentsu said the protest is against the continued looting at Eskom. According to Ngqentsu, Brian Molefe has been redeployed to open the funds of Eskom for looting. About &nbsp;50 SACP supporters gathered outside the CTICC with a strong police presence.They were holding up posters calling on Parliament to hold an enquiry into Eskom, Prasa and PetroSA. Private security was posted at every entrance of the building.CTICC spokesperson Susan Davis said they are in conversation with the event organisers to ensure the safety of delegates.Earlier on today, Davis said she was on the way to organise security on the convention floor.Protestors were asked to exit the convention square by police, when they shouted "Pantsi Eskom Pantsi.""Pantsi Jacob Zuma pantsi," was later shouted by protesters.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/malikanes-utterances-will-be-aligned-with-government-policies-gigaba-20170516